attributes.logicalName: Securitization Pool Loan Borrower Risk Category Code
attributes.gcd: Refers to the code pertaining to the risk category of the reference assets, which also constitute the risk category of the pool. The risk category for retail customers can be prime i.e. with code P, sub prime i.e. with code S and mid prime i.e. with code M. Prime indicates that these customers are very reliable, and there are hardly any chances of default. Subprime indicates that these customers are not eligible for loans, but have been provided loans at a higher cost, due to risk taking ability of bank. The mid prime indicates that these customers are not completely considered as prime, but also do not fit into the sub prime category. The wholesale customers do not have this category, as they are not assessed individually under these risk categories. Hence for the wholesale customers, it is only All i.e. with code A as a category.
